SIMPLE: revengeful
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Revengeful
<hw>Re*venge"ful</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Full of, or prone
to, revenge; vindictive; malicious; revenging; wreaking
revenge.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>If thy <qex>revengeful</qex> heart can not forgive.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>May my hands . . . ⟦br⟧
Never brandish more <qex>revengeful</qex> steel.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Vindictive; vengeful; resentful;
malicious.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Re*venge"ful*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Re*venge"ful*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Revengeless</ent>⟦br⟧
